<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Emergency Preparedness</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/emergency-prep.css">
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Georgia&family=Inter:wght@400;600&display=swap"
        rel="stylesheet">
</head>

<body>
    <nav class="lesson-nav">
        <a href="/dashboard/learn" class="back-btn">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"
                stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
                <path d="M19 12H5M12 19l-7-7 7-7" />
            </svg>
            Return to lessons
        </a>
        <h1>Emergency Preparedness Center</h1>
    </nav>

    <div class="knowledge-container">
        <article class="research-paper">
            <h1>Essential Emergency Readiness</h1>

            <div class="article-content">
                <section class="intro-section">
                    <p class="lead-paragraph">
                        Be ready for any crisis with proven preparedness strategies. This guide covers disaster
                        planning,
                        emergency kits, evacuation procedures, and life-saving first aid knowledge to protect your
                        family in critical situations.
                    </p>
                </section>

                <section class="main-content">
                    <h2>Emergency Kit Essentials</h2>
                    <p>
                        Build a 72-hour survival kit:
                    <ul class="emergency-list">
                        <li>Water (1 gallon/person/day)</li>
                        <li>Non-perishable food</li>
                        <li>First aid supplies</li>
                        <li>Emergency blanket</li>
                        <li>Portable radio</li>
                    </ul>
                    </p>

                    <h2>Disaster Preparedness</h2>
                    <p>
                        Specific threat planning:
                    <ul class="emergency-list">
                        <li>Earthquake: Secure heavy furniture</li>
                        <li>Wildfire: Defensible space</li>
                        <li>Flood: Elevation strategies</li>
                        <li>Power outage: Alternative lighting</li>
                    </ul>
                    </p>

                    <h2>Evacuation Planning</h2>
                    <p>
                        Create an effective exit strategy:
                    <ul class="emergency-list">
                        <li>Multiple escape routes</li>
                        <li>Family meeting points</li>
                        <li>Pet evacuation plans</li>
                        <li>Important document storage</li>
                    </ul>
                    </p>

                    <h2>Emergency Communication</h2>
                    <p>
                        Stay connected during crises:
                    <ul class="emergency-list">
                        <li>FEMA mobile app</li>
                        <li>Hand-crank radio</li>
                        <li>Out-of-area contact person</li>
                        <li>Emergency alert systems</li>
                    </ul>
                    </p>
                </section>
            </div>
        </article>

        <section class="health-interaction">
            <h2>Emergency Questions?</h2>
            <div class="query-container">
                <form action="/dashboard/learn/emergency/generate" method="POST">
                    <div class="input-group">
                        <textarea name="question" rows="4"
                            placeholder="Ask emergency prep questions (e.g., 'How to sanitize water in disasters?')"
                            aria-label="Emergency question input"></textarea>
                    </div>
                    <button type="submit" class="submit-btn">
                        Get Preparedness Info
                    </button>
                </form>

                <% if (responseText) { %>
                    <div class="response-card">
                        <div class="response-content">
                            <%= responseText %>
                                <p class="safety-note">Always follow official emergency directives during crises</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <% } %>
            </div>
        </section>
    </div>
</body>

</html>